        <p class="TableText">Opens the Formatting window pane, which has two tabs. The Style Inspector tab lets you see the style details for selected content in the open file (e.g., topic, snippet), and even edit those styles if necessary, without having to open the full stylesheet. The Local Properties tab displays local formatting for the selected content in a topic. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare-Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../../Flare/Styles/Other-Features-Activities/Regular-Stylesheets/Style-Inspector/Style-Inspector.htm">Style Inspector</MadCap:xref> and <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../../Flare/Local-Formatting/Local-Formatting.htm">Local Formatting</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Contributor">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../../Contributor/Styles/More/Using-Style-Inspector.htm">Using the Style Inspector</MadCap:xref> and <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../../Contributor/Local-Formatting/Local-Formatting.htm">Local Formatting</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
